<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384119>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Habitus photographs of Galbinocoris caepa, Hamatophylus guttulosus, Insulaphylus spp., Maculamiris spp., Quernocoris caliginosus, and Vesperocoris paddocki." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5384119/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384121>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Lateral aspect of head and pronotum, scanning micrographs, scale measurements in mm. A. Galbinocoris caepa. B. Hamatophylus guttulosus. C. Insulaphylus cruz. D. Maculamiris baja. E. Quernocoris caliginosus. F. Vesperocoris paddocki." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5384121/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384125>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Head and male genitalic structures of Insulaphylus spp. and Maculamiris spp. Insulaphylus cruz, head in frontal and lateral view, right and left paramere, phallotheca, and vesica; I. meridianus, vesica and apex of vesica in caudal view; Maculamiris baja, head in frontal and lateral view, right and left paramere, phallotheca, and vesica; M. insulanus, vesica." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5384125/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384139>
    dc:description "Fig. 11. Distribution of species of the genera Insulaphylus and Maculamiris. The species distributions are mapped onto distribution maps of some of their hosts." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5384139/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

